<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="92" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[130,777,854,1294]" box="[132,236,854,880]" pageId="27" pageNumber="92">FINDINGS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[130,777,854,1294]" pageId="27" pageNumber="92">
The 
<typeStatus box="[183,283,885,911]" pageId="27" pageNumber="92">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[325,441,886,911]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="27" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grimesii">
<emphasis box="[325,441,886,911]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="92">R. grimesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears flowering branches that somewhat resemble those of 
<taxonomicName box="[453,561,917,943]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="27" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="floridus">
<emphasis box="[453,561,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="92">R. floridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but they are more curved and the angles at which their inflorescences are held are mostly less acute. In addition, the prickles on their pedicels and inflorescence rachises are finely aciculate, quite unlike the strong, hooked prickles of the 
<taxonomicName box="[461,568,1044,1070]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="27" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="floridus">
<emphasis box="[461,568,1044,1070]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="92">R. floridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
type.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[130,777,854,1294]" pageId="27" pageNumber="92">
Since Enslen’s specimen lacks a primocane, any clear information about plant habit, or even details about geography, we cannot determine whether it is determinate side branch from a mounding dewberry (such as 
<taxonomicName box="[643,758,1173,1198]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="27" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grimesii">
<emphasis box="[643,758,1173,1198]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="92">R. grimesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), or from an atypical, upright 
<emphasis box="[448,597,1204,1230]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="92">Alleghenienses</emphasis>
(perhaps even a rare taxon in that section). Thus, we choose to maintain it as a 
<emphasis box="[180,356,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="92">nomen incertum</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
